AU  - Trojani, Fabio
T1  - When There Is No Place to Hide: Correlation Risk and the Cross-Section of Hedge Fund Returns
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht070
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
SP  - 581
EP  - 616
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a novel data set on correlation swaps, we study the relation between correlation risk, hedge fund characteristics, and their risk-return profile. We find that the ability of hedge funds to create market-neutral returns is often associated with a significant exposure to correlation risk, which helps to explain the large abnormal returns found in previous models. We also estimate a significant negative market price of correlation risk, which accounts for the cross-section of hedge fund excess returns. Finally, we detect a pronounced nonlinear relation between correlation risk exposure and the tail risk of hedge fund returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht070
ER  - 



